href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwestern-tanks-being-sent-to-ukraine-have-unique-maintenance-needs-2023-2%5C%22%3Ethe%20Abrams%20and%20Leopard%202%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20use%20in%20combat%20suggests%20either%20design%20or%20manufacturing%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20%26quot%3Bany%20T-14%20deployment%20is%20likely%20a%20high-risk%20decision%20for%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20British%20Defence%20Ministry%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1615955033668853760%2Fphoto%2F1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%20%26quot%3BEleven%20years%20in%20development%2C%20the%20program%20has%20been%20dogged%20with%20delays%2C%20reductions%20in%20planned%20fleet%20size%2C%20and%20reports%20of%20manufacturing%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20additional%20challenge%20for%20Russia%20is%20adapting%20its%20logistical%20chain%20to%20handle%20T-14%20because%20it%20is%20larger%20and%20heavier%20than%20other%20Russian%20tanks%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBudanov%20suggested%20that%20Moscow%20fears%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20T-14%20being%20destroyed%20or%20captured%2C%20a%20fate%20that%20has%20already%20befallen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-approaching-limit-of-ability-to-rebuild-tanks-ukraine-2023-8%5C%22%3Esome%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-approaching-limit-of-ability-to-rebuild-tanks-ukraine-2023-8%5C%22%3E%202%2C300%20other%20Russian%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20destroyed%20Armata%20would%20ruin%20the%20tank's%20%26quot%3Bexport%20attractiveness%2C%26quot%3B%20Budanov%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20T-14%20Armata%20tank%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6509bc48bf943d00195b9186%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221224%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20T-14%20on%20display%20at%20the%20International%20Military%20Forum%20Army%20outside%20Moscow%20on%20August%2015.%3Cp%3EALEXANDER%20NEMENOV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20shown%20off%20T-14s%20at%20arms%20shows%20in%20hopes%20of%20selling%20them%20to%20nations%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasiatimes.com%2F2023%2F02%2Frussia-wants-india-to-take-its-t-14-battle-tanks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndia%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20defray%20the%20cost%20of%20developing%20the%20pricey%20%E2%80%94%20by%20Russian%20standards%20%E2%80%94%20vehicle.%20Estimates%20put%20the%20cost%20of%20an%20Armata%20between%20%245%20million%20and%20%249%20million%2C%20compared%20to%20about%20%241%20million%20for%20a%20T-72%20and%20%243%20million%20for%20a%20T-80.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20which%20may%20be%20why%20the%20Russian%20army%20has%20retreated%20from%20an%20initial%20plan%20to%20buy%202%2C300%20Armatas%20by%202025.%20(The%20British%20Defence%20Ministry%20believes%20production%20is%20only%20in%20%26quot%3Bthe%20low%20tens.%26quot%3B)%20Not%20only%20is%20the%20T-14%20expensive%2C%20but%20Russian%20defense%20industry%20publications%20have%20reported%20development%20and%20manufacturing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-seems-uninterested-in-buying-its-own-t14-armata-tank-2022-8%5C%22%3Eproblems%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20the%20Armata%20is%20being%20%26quot%3Bfine-tuned%26quot%3B%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bthe%20results%20of%20its%20use%26quot%3B%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20a%20defense%20industry%20source%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.com%2Fdefense%2F1663335%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Tass%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August.%20The%20report%20didn't%20specify%20what%20modifications%20will%20be%20made%2C%20though%20RIA%20said%20in%20April%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussias-new-t-14-armata-battle-tank-debuts-ukraine-ria-2023-04-25%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadditional%20side%20armor%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20been%20fitted%20to%20the%20tanks%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20the%20West%20would%20not%20be%20wise%20to%20discount%20the%20Armata.%20It%20has%20several%20advanced%20features%20that%20will%20likely%20be%20found%20in%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20Western%20main%20battle%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20T-90M%20tank%20in%20Ukraine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62f59884f16a0d0018e63563%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20T-90M%20tank%20destroyed%20by%20Ukrainian%20forces%20in%20the%20Kharkiv%20region%20in%20May%202022.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FVitalii%20Hnidyi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20older%20Russian%20tanks%20had%20the%20commander%20and%20gunner%20in%20the%20turret%2C%20the%20T-14%20has%20an%20unmanned%20turret%20with%20a%20125-mm%20cannon%2C%20which%20the%20three-member%20crew%20remotely%20operates%20from%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20well-armored%20hull.%20The%20T-72%2C%20which%20has%20ammunition%20stored%20beneath%20the%20turret%2C%20is%20notorious%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbattlefield-video-shows-ukrainian-tank-defeating-russian-tank-2023-1%5C%22%3Eblowing%20its%20turret%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20being%20hit%20by%20enemy%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20advanced%20capabilities%20include%20on-board%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.armyrecognition.com%2Fnovember_2016_global_defense_security_news_industry%2Farmata-based_combat_vehicles_to_be_equipped_with_surveillance_drones_51811163.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereconnaissance%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20as%20automation%