s.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20amicus%20brief%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20from%2035%20former%20leaders%20from%20all%20four%20military%20branches%20who%20supported%20diversity.%20They%20referred%C2%A0to%20a%20period%20during%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20when%20a%20lack%20of%20diversity%20in%20military%20leadership%20led%20to%20racial%20tension%20among%20soldiers.%20Students%20for%20Fair%20Admissions%20argued%20that%20the%20issues%20those%20leaders%20referenced%20have%20%26quot%3Bnot%20existed%20for%20the%20past%20half%20century.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20the%20underlying%20assumption%20of%20West%20Point's%20argument%20is%20that%20soldiers%20view%20their%20peers%20and%20superiors%20foremost%20in%20terms%20of%20race%2C%20rather%20than%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20ability%20or%20character%20traits%20like%20loyalty%2C%20devotion%2C%20and%20selflessness%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20group%20said.%20%26quot%3BPut%20differently%2C%20it%20assumes%20that%20soldiers%20apply%20the%20same%20racial%20stereotypes%20to%20one%20another%20that%20West%20Point%20applies%20to%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWest%20Point%20has%20yet%20to%20file%20a%20response%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20first%20institution%20to%20be%20targeted%20since%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20affirmative%20action%20decision.%20Recently%2C%20Yale%20adjusted%20its%20admissions%20process%20to%20confirm%20it%20is%20not%20considering%20race%20at%20all%20when%20deciding%20to%20admit%20a%20student%2C%20leading%20Students%20for%20Fair%20Admissions%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2F07%2Faffirmative-action-lawsuit-dropped-yale-00114539%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrop%20the%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20filed%20against%20the%20Ivy%20League%20back%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20arguments%20for%20affirmative%20action%20in%20college%20admissions%20were%20not%20focused%20on%20the%20military%2C%20US%20Solicitor%20General%20Elizabeth%20Prelogar%20did%20touch%20on%20the%20issue%3A%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20United%20States%20military%2C%20as%20I've%20explained%2C%20having%20a%20diverse%20officer%20corps%20is%20a%20critical%20national%20security%20imperative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwest-point-affirmative-action-lawsuit-values-skin-color-over-loyalty-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695151971000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6509f37abf943d00195bd938%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwest-point-affirmative-action-lawsuit-values-skin-color-over-loyalty-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20group%20that%20won%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20affirmative%20action%20case%20is%20targeting%20West%20Point%2C%20saying%20military%20academies%20shouldn't%20consider%20race%20in%20admissions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwest-point-affirmative-action-lawsuit-values-skin-color-over-loyalty-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20NIL%20deals%20and%20brand%20sponsorships%20are%20helping%20college%20athletes%20make%20money%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22College%20Football%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F57fd79254046dd36318b4f39%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22689%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Halleran%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EStudent-athletes%20gained%20in%202021%20the%20right%20to%20make%20money%20from%20their%20names%2C%20images%2C%20and%20likenesses.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli