esn't%20want%20to%20occupy%20too%20much%20space%20in%20the%20industry.%20However%2C%20he%20did%20not%20rule%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20returning%20as%20Captain%20America%20in%20a%20future%20Marvel%20project.%20Rumors%20suggest%20his%20return%20in%20the%20upcoming%20film%20'Avengers%3A%20Secret%20Wars'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Fchris-evans-hints-at-filming-1-movie-a-year-after-marriage-to-alba-baptista-says-he-may-return-as-captain-america%2Farticleshow%2F103787246.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Women's%20Quota%20Bill%20-%20Will%20It%20Become%20Reality%20By%202029%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20gap%20of%2027%20years%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20hope%20again%20for%20the%20Women's%20Reservation%20Bill.%20In%20the%20last%20months%20of%20its%20second%20term%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20in%20office%20for%20nine%20years%2C%20has%20reignited%20hope%20for%20the%20long-pending%20bill%20guaranteeing%2033%20per%20cent%20quota%20for%20women%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies.%20The%20Union%20Cabinet%20approved%20the%20proposed%20bill%20on%20September%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20provides%20for%20a%20third%20of%20the%20reserved%20seats%20to%20be%20set%20aside%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes.%20There%20will%20be%20no%20quota%20for%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20state%20Legislative%20Councils.%20These%20reserved%20seats%20may%20be%20allotted%20by%20rotation%20to%20different%20constituencies%20in%20the%20state%20or%20Union%20Territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20have%2078%20women%20and%2031%20women%20members%2C%20which%20is%20merely%2014%20per%20cent%20of%20their%20total%20strength.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20state%20assemblies%20is%20less%20than%2015%20per%20cent.%20Despite%20various%20attempts%20at%20introducing%20the%20bill%20in%20the%20past%20to%20bring%20gender%20parity%20in%20parliament%20and%20state%20assemblies%2C%20the%20bill%20did%20not%20progress%20due%20to%20staunch%20opposition%20from%20parties%20like%20the%20RJD%20and%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20in%20Bihar%20and%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20of%20the%20day%20commands%20a%20majority%20and%20hopefully%2C%20the%20bill%20will%20be%20passed%20by%20both%20houses.%20It%20will%20provide%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20women%20to%20contest%20on%20the%20earmarked%20seats.%20When%20it%20becomes%20a%20law%2C%20it%20will%20be%20a%20great%20leap%20forward%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20women%20empowerment.%2033%20per%20cent%20constituencies%20reserved%20for%20women%20will%20be%20rotated%20after%20every%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20State%20Assembly%20elections%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Suman%20Kumar%2C%20Professor%2C%20Department%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20Rajdhani%20College%2C%20University%20of%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20demand%20from%20some%20political%20parties%20has%20always%20been%20to%20introduce%20'reservation%20within%20reservation'%20because%20the%20OBCs%2C%20SCs%20and%20STs%20are%20their%20major%20votebank.%20Keeping%20in%20view%20the%20Indian%20cultural%20set%20up%2C%20it%20is%20quite%20necessary%20to%20retain%20some%20quota%20system%20within%20this%20reservation%20system.%20The%20same%20system%20is%20working%20well%20in%20the%20Panchayati%20Raj%20System%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Kumar%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECuriously%2C%20the%20two%20largest%20parties%2C%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%2C%20have%20always%20supported%20the%20quota%20bill.%20Their%20allies%2C%20like%20the%20JD%20(U)%2C%20RJD%20and%20other%20parties%2C%20were%20the%20ones%20to%20put%20up%20roadblocks.%20The%20patriarchs%20of%20these%20parties%2C%20Lalu%20Yadav%20(RJD)%20and%20Mulayam%20Singh%20Yadav%20(Samajwadi%20Party)%2C%20belittled%20the%20bill%20saying%20it%20would%20only%20benefit%20%26quot%3Blipstick-wearing%2C%20short-haired%26quot%3B%20women%20from%20the%20upper%20castes%20and%20demanded%20a%20%26quot%3Bquota-within-quota%26quot%3B%20for%20OBC%20(Other%20Backward%20Class)%20women.%20The%20proposed%20bill%20is%20silent%20on%20including%20OBC%20women.%20The%20younger%20generation%2C%20represented%20by%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20(SP)%20and%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20(RJD)%2C%20backed%20the%20BRS'%20protest%20in%20Delhi%20in%20March%20in%20support%20of%20the%20bill.%20Their%20aim%20was%20ostensibly%20to%20project%20themselves%20as%20contemporary%20politicians%20with%20reformed%20views%20and%20to%20strike%20a%20common%20cause%20with%20the%20opposition%20bloc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20leaders%20are%20clever.%20They%20are%20not%20against%20the%20bill.%20Instead%2C%20they%20are%20pushing%20for%20reservation%20of%20downtrodden%20women%20in%20the%20overall%2033%20per%20cent%20seats%20to%20be%20reserved%20for%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Pradip%20Bhattacharya%2C%20former%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20West%20Bengal.%20Their%20demand%20for%20caste%20and%20community-based%20quota%20within%20the%20reservation%20block%20for%20women%20persists.%20%26quot%3BThe%20intent%20of%20this%20bill%20may%20be%20good%20but%20the%20practical%20political%20outcome%20may%20be%20far%20different%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20quota%20within%20the%20quota%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Dr%20Kumar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20was%20introduced%20on%20September%2012%2C%201996%2C%20by%20the%20Deve%20Gowda-led%20United%20Front%20government.%20It%20was%20introduced%20as%20the%2081st%20Constitution%20Amendment%20Bill%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20for%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20parliament.%20It%20failed%20to%20clear%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20test.%20The%20bill%20lapsed%20with%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20was%20reintroduced%20by%20the%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee-led%20NDA%20government%20in%201998.%20In%20an%20incident%20that%20brought%20disgrace%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20the%20bill%20was%20infamously%20snatched%20and%20torn%20by%20a%20RJD%20MP.%20The%20Vajpayee%20government%20failed%20in%20its%20attempts%20to%20table%20the%20bill%20in%201999%2C%202002%20and%202003.%20Then%20came%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh-led%20(UPA-1)%20government's%20turn%20to%20table%20the%20bill%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%20May%202008.%20It%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20standing%20committee.%20Since%20the%20bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20there%20was%20no%20fear%20of%20it%20lapsing.%20The%20bill%20was%20passed%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%20March%202010.%20The%20bill%20again%20lapsed%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20as%20it%20was%20opposed%20by%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20RJD%20(then%20a%20UPA%20ally)%20and%20JD(U)%2C%20an%20NDA%20ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20male%20politicians%2C%20for%20fear%20of%20their%20seats%20being%20earmarked%20as%20reserved%20for%20women%2C%20prevented%20women's%20quota%20from%20becoming%20a%20reality.%20However%2C%20not%20much%20noise%20was%20made%20in%201992-93%20against%20the%20constitutional%20amendment%20bills%2072%20and%2073%2C%20reintroduced%20by%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20government.%20The%20bills%20aimed%20to%20reserve%20a%20third%20(33%20per%20cent)%20of%20all%20seats%20and%20the%20chairperson%20posts%20for%20women%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20local%20bodies.%20This%20bill%20was%20initiated%20by%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%20in%201989%20to%20give%20women%20one-third%20reservation%20in%20rural%20and%20urban%20local%20bodies.%20Thanks%20to%20the%20reservation%2C%20there%20are%20nearly%2015%20lakh%20elected%20women%20representatives%20in%20panchayats%20and%20local%20bodies%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen's%20reservation%20in%20urban%20local%20bodies%20and%20panchayats%20have%20been%20impactful.%20A%20few%20uneducated%20women%20may%20be%20finding%20the%20administrative%20functioning%20difficult%20but%20the%20educated%20ones%20are%20doing%20better%20than%20their%20male%20counterparts.%20In%20fact%2C%20these%20women%2C%20whether%20as%20MPs%2C%20MLAs%20or%20members%20of%20local%20bodies%2C%20are%20balancing%20their%20roles%20at%20home%20and%20in%20office%20remarkably%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Bhattacharya.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20tried%20to%20secure%20the%20votes%20of%20women%20by%20tabling%20the%20bill%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20national%20election.%20The%20implementation%20of%20the%20bill%20is%20contingent%20upon%20the%20completion%20of%20the%20delimitation%20exercise%20of%20constituencies%2C%20which%20will%20begin%20not%20before%202027.%20There%20is%20slim%20chance%20of%20the%20bill%20becoming%20an%20Act%20before%202029.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695132240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fho7l0qc8_new-parliament-building_625x300_19_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwomens-quota-bill-will-it-become-reality-by-2029-4404632%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20a%20gap%20of%2027%20years%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20hope%20again%20for%20the%20Women's%20Reservation%20Bill.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwomens-quota-bill-will-it-become-reality-by-2029-4404632%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwomens-quota-bill-will-it-become-reality-by-2029-4404632%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwomens-quota-bill-will-it-become-reality-by-2029-4404632%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chandrababu%20Naidu%20case%3A%20What%20is%20the%20Andhra%20fibernet%20scam%20all%20about%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695132212000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103787564%2Cimgsize-11484.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fthird-graft-case-against-chandrababu-naidu-what-is-the-andhra-fibernet-scam-all-about%2Farticleshow%2F103787585.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20scam%20allegedly%20happened%20when%20Naidu%20was%20holding%20the%20portfolio%20of%20energy%2C%20infrastructure%20and%20investment%20department.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22U%20SUDHAKAR%20REDDY%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fthird-graft-case-against-chandrababu-naidu-what-is-the-andhra-fibernet-scam-all-about%2Farticleshow%2F103787585.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Pressing%20National%20Priority%E2%80%99%3A%20Canadian%20Newspapers%20React%20to%20Claims%20About%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20Killing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F19184738%2FHardeep-Singh-Nijjar.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Canadian%20newspapers%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20September%2019%2C%20said%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20was%20behind%20the%20killing%20of%20Sikh%20activist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20was%20%E2%80%9Cshocking%E2%80%9D%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20already%20strained%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20are%20set%20to%20take%20a%20turn%20for%20the%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20explosive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanada-accuses-indian-government-of-assassinating-sikh-citizen-in-vancouver-expels-senior-diplomat%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Canadian%20parliament%2C%20Trudeau%20claimed%20that%20Canadian%20security%20agencies%20are%20pursuing%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%20allegations%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20killing%20of%20Nijjar%20was%20linked%20to%20the%20Indian%20government.%20Nijjar%2C%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20is%20accused%20by%20India%20of%20leading%20a%20militant%20Khalistani%20group%20%E2%80%93%20an%20allegation%20he%20had%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENewspaper%20columnists%20and%20analysts%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20allegations%20are%20serious%20and%20unprecedented%20in%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20history.%20However%2C%20they%20also%20warned%20against%20lumping%20India%20together%20with%20China%20and%20Russia%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20foreign%20interference.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStunning%2C%20says%20Globe%20and%20Mail%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fpolitics%2Farticle-canada-is-once-more-thrust-into-a-new-world-of-foreign-intimidation%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGlobe%20and%20Mail%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20incident%20shows%20that%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20governments%20are%20continuing%20to%20reach%20into%20Canada%20to%20intimidate%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20never%20been%20anything%20like%20this%20before%3A%20an%20explosive%20public%20allegation%20that%20a%20foreign%20government%E2%80%99s%20agents%20targeted%20and%20killed%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20in%20Canada%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20Campbell%20Clark.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20not%20supposed%20to%20be%20an%20enemy%2C%20or%20even%20an%20adversary%E2%80%9D%20despite%20tensions%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20because%20the%20Indian%20government%20has%20for%20decades%20%E2%80%9Caccused%20Canada%20of%20being%20soft%20on%20Khalistani%20terrorists%E2%80%9D.%20The%20report%20adds%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20has%20often%20conflated%20non-violent%20Sikh%20separatist%20advocates%20with%20terrorists%20and%20extremists%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESaying%20that%20the%20idea%20that%20New%20Delhi%20might%20send%20agents%20to%20kill%20a%20Canadian%20in%20Canada%20is%20%E2%80%9Cstunning%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20newspaper%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CCanada%20is%20jolted%20into%20recognizing%20a%20new%20world%20in%20which%20foreign%20governments%20reach%20out%20to%20influence%2C%20intimidate%20and%20coerce%20Canadians%20in%20Canada.%20Again%2C%20there%20is%20new%20reason%20to%20believe%20foreign%20interference%20might%20be%20a%20bigger%2C%20broader%20danger%20than%20this%20country%20is%20prepared%20to%20counter.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20allegation%20is%20assassination%2C%20which%20underlines%20the%20direct%20threat%20to%20the%20security%20of%20Canadians%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20those%20who%20belong%20to%20diaspora%20communities%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20refers%20to%20previous%20incidents%20of%20foreign%20interference%20in%20Canada%20such%20as%20illegal%20Chinese%20police%20activity%20in%20several%20Canadian%20locations%20and%20attempts%20by%20Beijing%20to%20influence%20Canadian%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cexplosive%2C%20albeit%20unproven%2C%20allegation%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20newspaper%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20far%20from%20certain%20that%20the%20U.S.%20and%20other%20Canadian%20allies%20will%20rush%20to%20hold%20India%20to%20account%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20one%20thing%2C%20credible%20allegations%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20intelligence%20agencies%20aren%E2%80%99t%20the%20same%20as%20evidence%20gathered%20by%20police%20for%20a%20trial.%20And%20in%20a%20world%20where%20Western%20allies%20have%20imposed%20extensive%20economic%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%20and%20are%20increasingly%20seeking%20to%20counter%20China%E2%80%99s%20influence%2C%20the%20U.S.%20and%20European%20nations%20won%E2%80%99t%20relish%20the%20prospect%20of%20conflict%20with%20another%20major%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Cem%3EGlobe%20and%20Mail%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20if%20the%20allegation%20is%20true%2C%20it%20will%20be%20fuel%20for%20the%20coming%20public%20inquiry%20into%20foreign%20interference.%20Foreign%20governments%20apparently%20feel%20as%20though%20they%20can%20reach%20into%20Canada%20with%20impunity.%20Countering%20that%20is%20now%20a%20pressing%20national%20priority.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Could%20be%20a%20significant%20setback%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalpost.com%2Fnews%2Fcanada-india-relations-enflamed%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENational%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20claims%20are%20%E2%80%9Cjust%20the%20latest%20issue%20souring%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20much%20of%20which%20is%20centred%20around%20India%E2%80%99s%20accusations%20that%20Canada%20has%20tolerated%20the%20growth%20here%20of%20a%20violent%20Khalistan%20independence%20movement%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVivek%20Dehejia%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Carleton%20University%20who%20focuses%20on%20India%2C%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20because%20of%20the%20Trudeau%20government%E2%80%99s%20continuing%20focus%20on%20catering%20to%20the%20grievances%20of%20the%20voters%20%E2%80%9Cof%20the%20Sikh%20diaspora%20who%20are%20hostile%20to%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20historically%20important%20Liberal%20constituency%20is%20%E2%80%9Cintrinsically%20not%20very%20keen%20on%20(cozying)%20up%20with%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20could%20explain%20why%20the%20trade%20mission%20to%20India%20scheduled%20for%20the%20second%20week%20in%20October%20was%20abruptly%20cancelled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Miller%2C%20senior%20fellow%20and%20director%20of%20foreign%20affairs%20at%20the%20Macdonald-Laurier%20Institute%2C%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ENational%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20Can