tion-to-inflation%5C%22%3EModi%20government%20rushed%20to%20salvage%20its%20flagship%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20Scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20promised%20a%20small%20dip%20in%20process%2C%20of%20Rs%20200.%20But%20that%20is%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20the%20price%20increase%20of%20the%20last%20three%20years.%20The%20government%20has%20slashed%20subsidy%20on%20LPG%20to%20one-sixth%20since%202018-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20female%20workforce%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20female%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%20Rate%20(LFPR)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-is-indias-female-labour-force-participation-ratio-below-that-of-saudi-arabia-6619621.html%5C%22%3Eis%20much%20below%20that%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20Nepal%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20much%20lower%20than%20that%20of%20the%20East%20Asian%20nations%2C%20and%20the%20comparison%20with%20developed%20countries%20is%20even%20starker.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20notoriously%20low%20female%20LFPR%20has%20stagnated%2C%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmospi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublication_reports%2FAnnualReportPLFS2021-22F.pdf%5C%22%3EPeriodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS%20July%202021-June%202022)%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomen-labour-force-india-growth%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20CEDA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20data%20showed%20that%2029.4%25%20of%20women%20(aged%2015-59)%20were%20part%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20in%202021-22%2C%20as%20compared%20to%2029.8%25%20in%20the%20preceding%20year.%20In%20contrast%2C%20men%E2%80%99s%20LFPR%20improved%20from%2080.1%25%20in%202020-21%20to%2080.7%25%20in%202021-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20health%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unicef.org%2Findia%2Fwhat-we-do%2Fwomens-nutrition%5C%22%3ENational%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20NFHS-4%20(2015-