20the%20train%20ticket%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20mother%20had%20to%20pawn%20her%20last%20piece%20of%20jewellery%20%E2%80%94%20her%20nose%20ring%20%E2%80%94%20which%20got%20us%20Rs%202%2C000.%20I%20remember%20the%20bank%20manager%E2%80%99s%20expression%20when%20he%20saw%20the%20nose%20ring%2C%20knowing%20we%20had%20no%20other%20choice.%20I%20felt%20helpless%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls%20adding%20that%20the%20amount%20helped%20him%20with%20food%20and%20lodging%20for%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201991%2C%20he%20started%20his%20career%20as%20a%20private%20school%20teacher%20in%20Nagaland%20with%20a%20salary%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%20per%20month.%20He%20shares%20that%20this%20money%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20enough%20to%20cover%20his%20expenses%20as%20he%20sent%20some%20money%20back%20home%20too.%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20to%20pay%20Rs%20700%20per%20month%20for%20electricity%20and%20rent.%20How%20could%20I%20survive%20on%20just%20Rs%20300%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20started%20taking%20tuition%20for%20school%20students%20to%20supplement%20my%20income.%20I%20used%20to%20tutor%20from%206%20am%20to%2010%20am%2C%20then%20attend%20school%20until%204%20pm%2C%20and%20return%20to%20tutor%20again%20until%206%20pm.%20That%E2%80%99s%20how%20I%20managed%20for%20the%20first%20six%20years%20in%20private%20service%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20the%20teacher.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20also%20the%20time%20when%20Nagaland%20was%20facing%20insurgency%20issues.%20But%20the%20teacher%20didn%E2%80%99t%20let%20that%20hinder%20his%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201996%2C%20Nellayapan%20got%20a%20job%20as%20a%20postgraduate%20teacher%20in%20physics%20at%20the%20Government%20Higher%20Secondary%20School%20in%20Dimapur.%20In%201999%2C%20he%20got%20married%20and%20remembers%20how%20they%20then%20put%20an%20asbestos%20roof%20on%20their%20house.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20burden%20of%20responsibility%20is%20often%20a%20blessing.%20I%20had%20to%20move%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%2